she wants to feel beautiful i know somebody who has self esteem issues she is lbs and ' she looks at old pictures of herself and she wonders where she has gone wrong she is only i don't want her to struggle with these issues for the rest of her life she says don't even try to tell me i look good pictures don't lie she walks out of the house every morning sad and feels like everyones prettier than she is and that boys don't like her her sister is taller and leaner with a better figure and she is jealous she worries that she will never thin out and be fat and stuggle with weight she knows that its something to worry about and wants to be healthier but also be skinny she just doesn't feel beautiful what can i do to help her workout routines advice anyting she needs to lose maybe lbs and she feels fatter than she did at the beginning of the summer i want her to see all the beautiful things i see many young girls and boys face this issue i am an th grade teacher and unfortunately this attitude is not uncommon you can do many things to help her with self esteem but her own self worth must come from within i would suggest going out and doing active things play tennis volleyball dance you can do other activities that reflect inner beauty and talent painting play an instrument sing be a good example and skip the pizza chips and other foods that teenagers love to snack on when you hang out go to a healthy food store like trader joe's or whole foods and cook yummy but healthy snacks for when you hang out you are such a great friend if you are truly worried about your friends behavior and believe she may have an eating disorder or is becoming depressed tell your parents teacher or another trusted adult Friends Kodocha Teen Girl Squad Little Britain Obesity Cliff Richard Johnny the Homicidal Maniac Breastfeeding Binge eating disorder Anorexia nervosa FoxTrot Comanche The Fairly OddParents One Tree Hill (TV series) Garfield Infantilism Hypoglycemia Boston Public Camp Lazlo EastEn